{"info": {"author": "Shin-Wei Hwang", "author_email": "meebox@gmail.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "description": "# CJKStr -- A Simple Package for Processing CJK string\n\nIn Python, the string formatting function will treat a CJK characters as wide as a english letter.This make the result weired. For example:\n\n```Python\nprint(\"1234567890\" * 4) \na = \"\u6e2c\u8a66\"\nw = 10\nprint(f\"{a:{w}s}|\")\n```\n\nproduce output as this:\n\n```python\n1234567890123456789012345678901234567890\n\u6e2c\u8a66        |\n```\n\nThe width is setting to 10 in the formatting string. Since the 2 Chinese characters occupies 2 more spaces, the bar is printed in position 13.\n\nTo avoid this problem, we need to know how many CJK Chinese characters in the string and resuce the width accorantly.\n\nThis package has only one funcion:\n\n```python\ncount_cjk_chars(s) # return number of chinese characters in string s\n```\n\n### example\n```python\nimport cjkstr\n\nprint(\"1234567890\" * 4) \na = \"\u6e2c\u8a66\"\nw = 10\nprint(f\"{a:{w}s}|\")\nw = 10 - cjkstr.count_cjk_chars(a)\nprint(f\"{a:{w}s}|\")\n```\n\nouput:\n\n```python\n1234567890123456789012345678901234567890\n\u6e2c\u8a66        |\n\u6e2c\u8a66      |\n```\n\n\n\n", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/codemee/cjkstr", "keywords": "", "license": "", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "cjkstr", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/cjkstr/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/cjkstr/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/codemee/cjkstr"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/cjkstr/0.0.5/", "requires_dist": null, "requires_python": ">=3.0", "summary": "A simple package to processing CJK string", "version": "0.0.5", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>CJKStr -- A Simple Package for Processing CJK string</h1>\n<p>In Python, the string formatting function will treat a CJK characters as wide as a english letter.This make the result weired. For example:</p>\n<pre><span class=\"nb\">print</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s2\">\"1234567890\"</span> <span class=\"o\">*</span> <span class=\"mi\">4</span><span class=\"p\">)</span> \n<span class=\"n\">a</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"\u6e2c\u8a66\"</span>\n<span class=\"n\">w</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"mi\">10</span>\n<span class=\"nb\">print</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"sa\">f</span><span class=\"s2\">\"</span><span class=\"si\">{</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"si\">:{</span><span class=\"n\">w</span><span class=\"si\">}</span><span class=\"s2\">s</span><span class=\"si\">}</span><span class=\"s2\">|\"</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</pre>\n<p>produce output as this:</p>\n<pre><span class=\"mi\">1234567890123456789012345678901234567890</span>\n<span class=\"n\">\u6e2c\u8a66</span>        <span class=\"o\">|</span>\n</pre>\n<p>The width is setting to 10 in the formatting string. Since the 2 Chinese characters occupies 2 more spaces, the bar is printed in position 13.</p>\n<p>To avoid this problem, we need to know how many CJK Chinese characters in the string and resuce the width accorantly.</p>\n<p>This package has only one funcion:</p>\n<pre><span class=\"n\">count_cjk_chars</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">s</span><span class=\"p\">)</span> <span class=\"c1\"># return number of chinese characters in string s</span>\n</pre>\n<h3>example</h3>\n<pre><span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"nn\">cjkstr</span>\n\n<span class=\"nb\">print</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s2\">\"1234567890\"</span> <span class=\"o\">*</span> <span class=\"mi\">4</span><span class=\"p\">)</span> \n<span class=\"n\">a</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"\u6e2c\u8a66\"</span>\n<span class=\"n\">w</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"mi\">10</span>\n<span class=\"nb\">print</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"sa\">f</span><span class=\"s2\">\"</span><span class=\"si\">{</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"si\">:{</span><span class=\"n\">w</span><span class=\"si\">}</span><span class=\"s2\">s</span><span class=\"si\">}</span><span class=\"s2\">|\"</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"n\">w</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"mi\">10</span> <span class=\"o\">-</span> <span class=\"n\">cjkstr</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">count_cjk_chars</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"nb\">print</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"sa\">f</span><span class=\"s2\">\"</span><span class=\"si\">{</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"si\">:{</span><span class=\"n\">w</span><span class=\"si\">}</span><span class=\"s2\">s</span><span class=\"si\">}</span><span class=\"s2\">|\"</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</pre>\n<p>ouput:</p>\n<pre><span class=\"mi\">1234567890123456789012345678901234567890</span>\n<span class=\"n\">\u6e2c\u8a66</span>        <span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"n\">\u6e2c\u8a66</span>      <span class=\"o\">|</span>\n</pre>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 6888319, "releases": {"0.0.1": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "731032fd134964054be47f41d1a8f56c", "sha256": "b0abd78a6aca142270f7b924dbe97decab810ab26d59b1855352085eb601b0cd"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "cjkstr-0.0.1-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "731032fd134964054be47f41d1a8f56c", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3", "requires_python": ">=3.0", "size": 2691, "upload_time": "2020-03-24T10:45:00", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-03-24T10:45: